  "name": "Yatūlun, Chain of Thorns",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "<p><em>Yatūlun</em> is focused on the safety and protection of the Bloodbloom and the people of Geb. It imparts the following edicts and anathema on the wielder. If they're violated, the artifact reverts to its non-artifact form until the wielder atones, either through the use of the atone ritual, or through a short side quest or influence encounter of your own design.</p><p><span style=\"border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-size:16px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;outline:0px\"><strong>Edicts</strong> protect undead from persecution, guard those you love, and oppose corruption wherever it is found</span></p><p><span style=\"border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-size:16px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;outline:0px\"><strong>Anathema</strong> persecute the undead, side with absuers or the corrupt, abandon those you love</span><span style=\"border:0px;font-family:inherit;font-size:16px;font-style:inherit;font-weight:inherit;margin:0px;padding:0px;vertical-align:baseline;outline:0px\">, allow your hungers to endanger your comrades</span></p><h2>Choose Apex Attribute</h2><p><em>Yatūlun</em> is a powerful apex item, but the apex bonuses granted are more powerful than most. As with all apex items, a PC can only benefit from one apex item at a time. When your character creates the artifact, choose one attribute modifier. When you invest the artifact, you either increase that attribute modifier by 2 or increase it to +5, whichever would give you a higher value. Once you make this selection, you can't change it later.</p><hr /><p><em>Note: Select the apex attribute on the details tab of this item.</em></p><h2>Choose Heroic Skill</h2><p><em>Yatūlun</em> also bolsters one skill of your choice. When your character creates the artifact, choose one of the three skills listed for the artifact. As long as the artifact is invested by you, it grants you a +4 item bonus to checks with that skill.</p><h2>Heroic Recovery</h2><p>Finally, <em>Yatūlun</em> has 1 Recovery Point; this point replenishes once per day when its invested partner does their daily preparations. When the artifact's partner's @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.3uh1r86TzbQvosxv]{Doomed} value would reach an amount sufficient to kill them (usually 4), the artifact spends its Recovery Point, and the partner instead reduces their @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.3uh1r86TzbQvosxv]{Doomed} value by 1 and stabilizes at 0 Hit Points.</p><h2>Invested Weapon</h2><p>Note that normally staves and weapons don't need to be invested, but <em>Yatūlun</em> is an exception to this rule. It provides its constant benefits as long as the item remains invested and is carried or stowed by a character; they need not be held in a hand or wielded as a weapon in combat in order to grant these benefits. If you drop an invested staff or weapon, are disarmed of it, or otherwise release it from being held or stowed, you continue to benefit from its invested qualities until the end of your next turn—if you reclaim the staff or weapon before the end of your next turn, then your investment continues uninterrupted. If you fail to reclaim the item by this point, it's no longer invested until you repeat the process by Interacting with the item, taking the normal steps to invest the item.</p><h2>Intelligent Weapon</h2><p><strong>Perception</strong> [[/r 1d20+34 #Perception]]{+34}; precise darkvision and hearing within 30 feet</p><p><strong>Communication</strong> telepathy (partner only)</p><p><strong>Skills</strong> Geb Lore [[/r 1d20+35 #Geb Lore]]{+35}, Society [[/r 1d20+34 #Society]]{+34}, Intimidation [[/r 1d20+33 #Intimidation]]{+33}</p><p><strong>Int</strong> +5, <strong>Wis</strong> +6, <strong>Cha</strong> +7</p><p><strong>Will</strong> [[/r 1d20+34 #Will]]{+34}</p>",
      "value": "<p>This weapon, crafted from a rare, black alloy with silvery veins, and was attuned to Idumea by her loving wife Sifra, and good friend Harwen, is a +3 <em>greater striking soulsteel asp coil</em>. It seems to dance and lunge, like a beautiful serpent, and is covered in what appear to be sharp thorns that dig into its targets, drawing bloody wounds. <em>Yatūlun </em>has the grapple trait. On a critical hit, or when you critically succeed at a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.PMbdMWc2QroouFGD]{Grapple} check using <em>Yatūlun</em>, it deals @Damage[2d6[bleed]] damage. <em>Yatūlun</em> has been partially alloyed with a sacred, secret alloy that makes the blade count as both cold iron and silver.</p><hr /><p><strong>Activate - Enchain</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1 </span>(concentrate, manipulate)</p><p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per hour</p><p><strong>Effect </strong>Make a melee strike at a target within 60 feet, on a success the blade wraps around them and makes them @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} until the end of your next turn.</p><hr /><p><strong>Activate - Reel</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1 </span>(concentrate, manipulate)</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong> You have @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} a target with Enchain</p><p><strong>Effect</strong> On a failed @Check[fortitude|against:class-spell] save, the target is pulled directly towards the wielder, to within their reach. The target then loses the Immobilized condition. This counts as forced movement.</p><hr /><p><strong>Activate - Cast</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">1 </span>(concentrate, manipulate)</p><p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p><p><strong>Requirements</strong> You have @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} a target with Enchain</p><p><strong>Effect </strong>You move directly towards the target, ending your movement within reach of the target. The target loses its @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.eIcWbB5o3pP6OIMe]{Immobilized} condition. You do not trigger reactions from movement during this action.</p><p></p><hr /><p>When drawn, this weapon seems to pull in the sound around it, making everything quieter.</p>"
    },
